<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1761,1932]" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,554,1761,1788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Rationale for the synonymies.</emphasis>
We recognize here the coarsely granular brown 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[1096,1205,1762,1788]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Cosmetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="4" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1096,1205,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Cosmetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Eastern 
<collectingRegion box="[1364,1432,1761,1787]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, profusely and variably sprinkled with golden-white dots and wavy reticles as Perty’s 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[1122,1226,1798,1824]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Cosmetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="4" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varius">
<emphasis box="[1122,1226,1798,1824]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">C. varius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The color pattern varies from a well-developed complex mask, covering the animal’s entire body and giving it a honeycombed appearance (
<figureCitation box="[268,353,1869,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,562,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-193@7.[151,1436,561,1917]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5A−D. Cosmetus acanti sp. nov.: (A) Male holotype (MPUJ_ENT 58151), dorsal view. (B) same, frontal view. (C) same, lateral view showing spine length (SL). (D) female paratype (MPUJ_ENT 47575), dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5120723" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5120723/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Fig 5A</figureCitation>
), to a more dissociated pattern (
<figureCitation box="[724,818,1869,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1619,1643]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,555,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-146@4.[151,1435,554,1595]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2A−D. Living specimens of Cosmetus spp. from Atlantic Forest in Brazil. (A−B) C. delicatus from Espírito Santo. (C) C. arietinus, from Espírito Santo. (D) C. varius from Bahia. Photos by Miguel Medrano &amp; Adriano Kury (A–B) and courtesy of Marcos Martinelli (C) and Airton Carvalho (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5120717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5120717/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Figs 2D</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[877,912,1869,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,562,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-193@7.[151,1436,561,1917]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5A−D. Cosmetus acanti sp. nov.: (A) Male holotype (MPUJ_ENT 58151), dorsal view. (B) same, frontal view. (C) same, lateral view showing spine length (SL). (D) female paratype (MPUJ_ENT 47575), dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5120723" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5120723/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">5B</figureCitation>
), where the animal is more “bicolor” like the average cosmetid.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5120719" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5120719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5120719/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" startId="5.[151,250,834,858]" targetBox="[152,1435,181,810]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,834,894]" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,324,834,858]" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">FIGURE 3A−E.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[330,497,834,857]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Cosmetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varius">
<emphasis box="[330,497,834,857]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">Cosmetus varius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from ZMB with labels, from Brazil, Bahia. A−D. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1839" box="[1002,1162,834,858]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Cosmetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesacanthus">
<emphasis box="[1002,1162,834,858]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">C. mesacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ZMB 951) ID by Roewer. E−H. Syntypes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sorensen" authorityYear="1932" box="[339,501,870,894]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Cosmetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pleurostigma">
<emphasis box="[339,501,870,894]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">C. pleurostigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ZMB 952). Courtesy of Anja Friederichs &amp; Jason Dunlop.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,940,1290]" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">
If we follow the itinerary of Spix &amp; von Martius in their Brazilian Expedition (
<figureCitation box="[1084,1184,940,966]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1437,1461]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,460,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-153@13.[162,1425,453,1413]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 11A−D. Distribution of Cosmetus. (A) known distribution of species currently included in Cosmetus. (B) detail of Panama and Colombia. (C) Brazilian species compared with itinerary of Spix and von Martius expedition. (D) detail of species in Bahia and Espírito Santo states (except for C. unispinosus and C. soerenseni with the vague locality “Bahia”)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5120737" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5120737/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
), it is easy to note that they bypassed Espírito Santo and bisected Bahia ending up in 
<collectingCountry box="[857,958,976,1002]" name="El Salvador" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">Salvador</collectingCountry>
, which is entirely consistent with our proposed identification of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[414,517,1012,1038]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Cosmetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varius">
<emphasis box="[414,517,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">C. varius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Perty, J. A. M." box="[533,732,1012,1039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" refId="ref9807" refString="Perty, J. A. M. (1833) Delectus animalium articulatorum, quae in itinere per Brasiliam annis MDCCCXVII-MDCCCXX [1817 - 1820] jussu et auspiciis Maximiliani Josephi I Bavariae Regis augustissimi peracto, collegerunt Dr. J. B. de Spix et Dr. C. F. Ph. de Martius. Vol. 3. [Opiliones, pp 201 - 209]. [&quot; 1830 - 1834 &quot;]. Friedrich Fleischer, Monachii [Munchen], 224 pp., pls. 25 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 102991" type="book" year="1833">Perty (1833: 203)</bibRefCitation>
characterized 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[898,1002,1012,1038]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Cosmetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varius">
<emphasis box="[898,1002,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">C. varius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as follows: “Fuscus, margine undique et punctis numerosis dorsalibus albidis”, which does not match the “redescription” of this species as given by C.L. 
<bibRefCitation author="Koch, C. L." box="[151,353,1084,1110]" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" pagination="107 - 158" refId="ref8806" refString="Koch, C. L. (1840) s. n. In: Die Arachniden getreu nach der Natur abgebildet und beschrieben. Vol. 7. Part 6. C. H. Zeh'schen Buchhandlung, Nurnberg, pp. 107 - 158, 6 pls." type="journal article" year="1840">Koch (1840: 109)</bibRefCitation>
. Koch’s description and illustration of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[787,889,1084,1110]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Cosmetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varius">
<emphasis box="[787,889,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">C. varius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
correspond to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Soares &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="1946" box="[1056,1272,1084,1110]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Cosmetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delicatus">
<emphasis box="[1056,1272,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">Cosmetus delicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
instead. However, Koch mentions that his 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1839" box="[476,653,1120,1146]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Cosmetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesacanthus">
<emphasis box="[476,653,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">C. mesacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is yellow. 
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer, C. F." box="[772,940,1120,1147]" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref10053" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1912) Die Familie der Cosmetiden Opiliones-Laniatores. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 78 (10), 1 - 122." type="journal article" year="1912">Roewer (1912)</bibRefCitation>
followed Koch blindly. We do not think that either has recognized the true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[495,599,1156,1182]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Cosmetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varius">
<emphasis box="[495,599,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">C. varius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which we deem to be the same species as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1839" box="[1097,1276,1156,1182]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Cosmetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesacanthus">
